Mix @flour{3%cups}, @baking soda{1%teaspoon}, @cinnamon{1%teaspoon},
@sugar{2%cups}, and @salt{1%teaspoon} together.

Make a hole in the center of the mixture.

Pour @sliced strawberries{2x 10%oz packages}, @vegetable oil{1 and 1/4%cups},
and @well-beaten eggs{4} into the hole.

Mix by hand until all inggredients are thoroughly combined.

Pour into two ungreased and floured #9x5x3 inch pans{}.

Bake in an #oven at (350 degrees) for
~{40%minutes} to ~{60%minutes}.
